<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05069f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05069f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05069f"> 69(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> M &amp; By&apos;s eyes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The explanation <font color="green">[for the fact that babies start with labials]</font> has been given that the child can see the working of his mother&apos;s lips in these sounds and therefore imitates her movements. &hellip; Moreover, it has been pointed out that the child&apos;s attention is hardly ever given to its mother&apos;s mouth, but is steadily fixed on her eyes. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJLN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJLN"><cite title="source">Language: its Nature, Development and Origin</cite></a> (Jan 1922) 105</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
